Sec. 55.004. CAPITAL STOCK. (a) Except as provided by
Subsection (b) of this section, an association may be organized under
this chapter with or without capital stock.
(b) If an association formed under this chapter is organized to
lend money secured by chattel mortgages on livestock, the association
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 278 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

shall be organized with capital stock.
(c) An association formed under this chapter with capital stock
automatically shall increase its stock at the rate of 10 percent of
the amount of loans or discounts made by the association to its
members.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1122, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

